result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

On motion of the state and pursuant to negotiations, court ordered case dismissed and read-in for sentencing purposes.

Attorney Brian Christopher Hagner in court, defendant Timothy Alan Taylor not in court, in custody.  William P. Dockry appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: KAR.
Defendant in custody not produced, appearance waived.  Case calendared for scheduling conference.  Defense requests final pretrial conference and jury trial dates.  State does not object.  Court ordered case adjourned for final pretrial conference and jury trial in Branch 36.  Final pre-trial scheduled for June 21, 2016 at 08:30 am.  Jury trial scheduled for July 13, 2016 at 08:30 am.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with S.M. dob 2/21/1973.

Court orders defendant TURNED OVER to JUSTICE Point for Supervision. The Court ordered defendant to maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY. No use or possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription. No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms. Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings. Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Timothy Alan Taylor in court with attorney Mary Garvin Guimont.  Defendant Timothy Alan Taylor in custody.  Mark Patrick Dooley appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Kremers, Branch 36.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Scheduling conference scheduled for May 9, 2016 at 08:30 am.
